  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - The proposed scheme by virtue of its design would introduce excessive visual clutter and would be an incongruous additions, which would harm the character, appearance and pedestrian experience of this section of the public streetscene. The proposal is therefore contrary to Local Plan policies CC1 (Context and Character), and CC2 (Urban design and architecture). ",
    "Reason : 2 - The proposed scheme would result in the loss of the existing formalised pedestrian access into the site. It considered that the proposed development would not support the Council's objectives of promoting trips by sustainable and active modes, and as such would be contrary to Local Plan Policy EC2 (Developing a sustainable local transport network). ",
    "Reason : 3 - The applicant has not demonstrated that the proposal would not negatively impact the existing fire safety strategy for this site. The proposal would therefore not comply with policy D12a of the London Plan."
